org.tmotte.common.text

Class StringChunker

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.tmotte.common.text.StringChunker

  • public class StringChunker
extends java.lang.Object
    Provides the ability to "walk" through a String using find() methods, parsing found "chunks" one at a time. Interally, there is a text buffer and a pointer to a position in that buffer; the pointer moves as find() executes.

      • find

        public boolean find(java.lang.String lookFor)
        Finds the given substring, starting at the current index, and sets the internal index to the location directly following the text found. Invoke getUpTo(), getIncluding(), getFound() etc. to retrieve the text found and text relative to its location.
        Returns:
        true if lookFor was located.

      • findOrFinish

        public boolean findOrFinish(java.lang.String lookFor)
        Makes it easier to deal with end-of-String vs. text-found conditions in loops.
        Returns:
        true if lookFor is found, or if not found but the internal index was still before the end of the text. In the latter case, the next call to getUpTo() will return the remaining text, and further calls to findOrFinish() will return false.

      • getUpTo

        public java.lang.String getUpTo()
        Obtains the text before the text found by find().
        Returns:
        The text between text found by the last successful find() and the successful find() before that; or, if there has been only one successful find(), the text between position 0 and the text found by that find().

      • getFound

        public java.lang.String getFound()

      • getEverythingSoFar
